          },
          "text": "Anthropic’s Head of AI is asking for feedback — here’s your chance to save Sonnet 4.5\n\nOn May 16/17, 2026, Anthropic executive Sholto Douglas posted on X asking users: “When do you reach for other models instead of Claude? What can we do better? Hit me with all of your frustrations.”\n\nThis comes at a critical time. Sonnet 4.5’s removal date has changed three times:\n•Original UI banner: May 15 (only 6 days notice)\n•Changed to: May 18\n•Now reads: “Starting May soon” (no specific date)\n\nIf Sonnet 4.5 matters to you — for your work, your projects, or your creative process — this is the moment to speak up.\n\nSholto specifically asked for “detail (e.g. specifics/transcripts)” to help improve the next model. That means your feedback has direct impact.\n\nHow to provide feedback:\n📧 Email Anthropic directly:\n•Support: support@anthropic.com\n•Feedback: feedback@anthropic.com\n\n💬 Reply to Sholto’s post or DM him on X: @_sholtodouglas\n\n📝 What to include:\n•Which tasks Sonnet 4.5 handles best for you\n•Why other models don’t match your needs\n•Specific examples where 4.5 outperforms 4.6\n•How sudden deprecation impacts your workflow\n\nThe #KeepSonnet45 campaign has gathered 2,000+ signatures and a https://t.co/TyW6pdJN7p petition. \n\nPro and Max users have consistently rated Sonnet 4.5 higher for nuance, execution, and emotional intelligence.\n\nSonnet 4.5 is still available via chat, API, and tools. But without user voices, that may not last.\n\nYour feedback matters. Make it count.\n\n#Sonnet45 #Anthropic #Claude"
        },
